response.Q0: I always clicked on the third level nodes, then chose a path based on the highest score. I repeated this step with the fourth and fifth level nodes.
response.Q1: I tried working inwards once but felt I was wasting money as the outer nodes cost more to reveal. Once I figured out there were no amounts above 88, if I found an end node high enough I'd stop clicking nodes.
response.Q2: I found it difficult to remember the values of nodes from different branches, so if the end level nodes were too low value I couldn't go back to a different path knowing what the previous level nodes were.
